laL3U","ref":"1Kgs.22.4","text":"And he said unto Jehoshaphat, Wilt thou go with me to battle to Ramothgilead? And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, I am as thou art, my people as thy people, my horses as thy horses.","year":-897},{"id":"recfeuDluaBsd5Ri0","ref":"1Kgs.22.5","text":"And Jehoshaphat said unto the king of Israel, Enquire, I pray thee, at the word of the LORD to day.","year":-897},{"id":"recusULzQcw7QWnKi","ref":"1Kgs.22.6","text":"Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four hundred men, and said unto them, Shall I go against Ramothgilead to battle, or shall I forbear? And they said, Go up; for the Lord shall deliver it into the hand of the king.","year":-897},{"id":"rec3RRfxo1XAPBlnl","ref":"1Kgs.22.7","text":"And Jehoshaphat said, Is there not here a prophet of the LORD besides, that we might enquire of him?","year":-897},{"id":"rec4JkRN2qb6s4rcp","ref":"1Kgs.22.8","text":"And the king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat, There is yet one man, Micaiah the son of Imlah, by whom we may enquire of the LORD: but I hate him; for he doth not prophesy good concerning me, but evil. And Jehoshaphat said, Let not the king say so.","year":-897}]}
